To match the expected B2Boost context, extend it with the fields Arthur already knows.

```java
@Data
@JsonIgnoreProperties(ignoreUnknown = true)
public class HandoffExchangeResponse {

    @JsonProperty("user_id")
    private String userId;          // GPS number / internal user identifier

    @JsonProperty("username")
    private String username;        // Login IS

    @JsonProperty("email")
    private String email;

    @JsonProperty("first_name")
    private String firstName;

    @JsonProperty("last_name")
    private String lastName;

    @JsonProperty("brand_context")
    private String brandContext;    // for example ORANGE / CETELEM

    @JsonProperty("app_id")
    private String appId;

    @JsonProperty("selected_sales_point_id")
    private String selectedSalesPointId;

    @JsonProperty("selected_org_unit_id")
    private String selectedOrgUnitId;

    @JsonProperty("roles")
    private List<String> roles;

    @JsonProperty("session_expires_at")
    private Instant sessionExpiresAt;

    @JsonProperty("token_expires_at")
    private Instant tokenExpiresAt;
}
```

Then update `HandoffService.exchange(...)` where you build the response:

```java
HandoffExchangeResponse response = new HandoffExchangeResponse();

response.setUserId(session.getUserId());
response.setUsername(session.getUsername());
response.setEmail(session.getEmail());
response.setFirstName(session.getFirstName());
response.setLastName(session.getLastName());

response.setBrandContext(session.getBrandContext());
response.setAppId(session.getAppId());

response.setSelectedSalesPointId(session.getSelectedSalesPointId());
response.setSelectedOrgUnitId(session.getSelectedOrgUnitId());

response.setRoles(session.getRoles());

response.setSessionExpiresAt(session.getExpiresAt());
response.setTokenExpiresAt(session.getTokenExpiresAt());

return response;
```

Use the exact getter names from your `UserSession`; they may differ slightly.

A likely returned payload becomes:

```json
{
  "user_id": "12345678",
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "test.user@example.com",
  "first_name": "Test",
  "last_name": "User",
  "brand_context": "CETELEM",
  "app_id": "B2BOOST_BE",
  "selected_sales_point_id": "SP001",
  "selected_org_unit_id": "OU001",
  "roles": ["SALES_ADVISOR"],
  "session_expires_at": "2026-06-25T17:00:00Z",
  "token_expires_at": "2026-06-25T16:30:00Z"
}
```

Two important points:

* Do **not** return the Ping access token, ID token, refresh token, Arthur session ID, or handoff code.
* Only add `session_expires_at` and `token_expires_at` if B2Boost confirms it needs them. B2Boost should create and manage its own session after successful exchange.

